$interpreted: Tindoiimu: Remember, people need to think you're dead. Find a place to hide. Don't stay here, and don't go back to the tribe.
Tindoiimu: I'll go talk to the arbiter. There should still be some room for compromise in this war.
Jiyanama: They... I'm so sorry for all of this trouble.
Tindoiimu: It's ok, Jiyanama. I've been a hostage for this long... I'm used to trouble.
Jiyanama: I'm so sorry. I've failed you. Will you forgive me?
Jiyanama: Maybe it's too late now, but... I raised you. You're a part of me...
Qilin Soldier: Hey, you're finally out!
Jiyanama: Qilin troops? How did they know we were here?
Tindoiimu: ......
Qilin Soldier: What are you doing!?
Tindoiimu: I'm the princess of the Insect Tribe. If you want a war with us, I'm your most valuable bargaining chip.
Tindoiimu: If something happens to me, then who would take responsibility!?
Tindoiimu: Jiyanama, get out of here, now!
Jiyanama: But, I can't leave—
Qing Feng: What nonsense.
Jiyanama: —you alone again...
Tindoiimu: ......
Qing Feng: Does the princess not know?
Qing Feng: This morning, while you were messing around in the waterfall, the Alliance attacked the Insect Tribe. It was a decisive victory.
Qing Feng: The insect king and queen, along with most of their subjects, have paid their debts.
Tindoiimu: Paid... their debts?
Qing Feng: I wouldn't expect some uneducated maggot like you to understand...
Qing Feng: Yes, their debts. They've given their lives to atone for their transgressions. As has this filthy spy.
Tindoiimu: ...Nana... father... mother...
Tindoiimu: our subjects... they're all dead?
Qing Feng: Well, not everybody. Your sister escaped with a few in tow. Isn't that just like a bug? Despicable, but to be expected.
Tindoiimu: ......
Tindoiimu: ...No... this isn't real!
Tindoiimu: This isn't happening!!
Qing Feng: But I'm afraid it is. And now the Alliance has no further need of you.
Qing Feng: So I'm afraid I'll have to exterminate you, like the rest of your kind.
Qing Feng: Everyone! Kill her!
Tindoiimu: The East Alliance... is nothing but a cesspool of false kings and false gods!
Qing Feng: Kong Maeok! What are you doing here!?
Maeok: I'd like to ask you the same thing!
Maeok: Do you forget that all who pass through the waterfall and claim the Holy Talisman can join the Martial Arts Tournament?
Maeok: Regardless of past crimes or status. And has Princess Tindoiimu not successfully passed the trials?
Qing Feng: —How would you know that!?
Juan Yun: —I told her!
Juan Yun: ...You shattered the final illusion, by yourself, and are worthy of the Holy Talisman.
Juan Yun: That final mirrored tile you stepped on, it showed your face to everyone in the Qilin Tribe.
Tindoiimu: ......
Juan Yun: ...Give me your blade. You shouldn't be holding something so dangerous.
Tindoiimu: ......
Maeok: And the first thing you do, chieftain, instead of telling your arbiter, is try to march in here and kill the victor?
Maeok: The princess may not know these rules, but for our chieftain to disobey them... how will you explain yourself to the tribes?
Qing Feng: ......
Tindoiimu: ......
Qing Feng: ...Don't let my disobedient son fool you. Give up the talisman, and I'll spare your life.
Maeok: Chieftain! Have respect!
Qing Feng: You have respect! You're the one who wants to allow a maggot to sully the traditions of our tribe.
Qing Feng: Know that this tournament is filled with our fiercest warriors. You'll surely die, or come close to it.
Qing Feng: Even if you do make it through, I will dog your every waking hour. I will give you a life worse than death.
Tindoiimu: ...Why?
Qing Feng: ...What?
Tindoiimu: Why can't you just leave me? Just let me be?
Qing Feng: For our tribe's name, of course. Your very existence is heresy.
Qing Feng: You cannot be allowed to live.
Tindoiimu: ...I understand.
Juan Yun: Princess?
Qing Feng: Finally, some reason.
Tindoiimu: I understand my father was wrong. No matter how low we hung our heads, you would have never pardoned us.
Qing Feng: You...
Maeok: ......
Tindoiimu: And I understand Jiyanama was right. Those captured would never return.
Tindoiimu: But if that means we have to lay down and die—become your property...
Tindoiimu: ...Then hell with it! Maybe revenge is all we have left!
Qing Feng: You... insolent...!
Tindoiimu: I will accept this talisman, and join your tournament.
Tindoiimu: Then, when I win and become the Alliance's new arbiter, I will cut down your precious Udumbara tree myself!
Tindoiimu: And like a poison, we will cover this land! The Insect Tribe will rule the east!
